          "text": "The user is asking about whether execution policy is set in profiles. This is a factual question about PowerShell. Let me answer concisely.\n\nNo, execution policy is NOT set in profiles. It's stored in the Windows registry (or an environment variable on Linux/macOS) and is set via `Set-ExecutionPolicy`, not in profile scripts.\n\nActually, I should give a slightly more nuanced answer. The execution policy is a machine-level or user-level setting stored in the registry, and it's read by PowerShell before any profile scripts are loaded. Profiles cannot override it because the policy is checked before profiles run. However, you can technically set it from within a profile if you have the rights, but that's not the intended mechanism.",
